—— l. 14. provinciales ordinum, etc. The provincial of the Carmelites in England at this time was John Baconthorp, who died in 1346. ‘He was little of stature, but great in wit, and writ such vast volumes that his body could not have borne what his brain produced.'—Stevens, Hist.
